  "body": "Hi,\r\n**Geth 1.10.26** is not working on my **Linux** and I would like to know if the problem is mine or not.\r\nI was able to sync blocks until 2 months ago but after that Geth gets stuck in \"Looking for peers\" forever...\r\n\r\n<img width=\"607\" alt=\"Screenshot 2022-12-31 at 16 36 32\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31778602/210144628-f507351c-1769-40f1-b710-0340f8645efd.png\">\r\n\r\nI wanted to know if anyone else had this problem.\r\nI'm running geth in light mode: **./geth --syncmode light**\r\n\r\nI have these ports enabled: \r\n30303/tcp\r\n30303/udp\r\n30304/tcp\r\n30304/udp\r\n8546/tcp\r\n\r\nI also tried to remove the db and resync again: **./geth removedb --datadir=~/.ethereum**\r\n...but the problem persists. I can sync some blocks up to 2-3 months ago and then it gets stuck...\r\n\r\nAny idea?\r\n",
